Cisówek  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dubeninki, within Gołdap County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  south of Dubeninki,  east of Gołdap, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
